19/07/2007
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Parliament confirmed on Wednesday (July 18th) proposed personnel and structural changes in the coalition cabinet. Two ministers have resigned over the past couple of months -- Economy and Energy Minister Rumen Ovcharov and Justice Minister Georgi Petkanov. Ovcharov will be replaced by Petar Dimitrov, while Petkanov's post will go to Miglena Tacheva. More cabinet changes are expected this autumn. (Sega, Monitor, Dnevnik - 19/07/07; Darik, Makfax - 18/07/07)
